The paper deals with decoding of non-binary LDPC codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of truncated messages is a technique commonly used in network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses complexity analysis, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, LDPC codes are commonly used in communication systems (cs.SY).
